Package fr.sekelenao.skcsv

Class SkCsvRow

java.lang.Object
fr.sekelenao.skcsv.SkCsvRow
All Implemented Interfaces:
Iterable<String>, RandomAccess
public class SkCsvRow extends Object implements Iterable<String>, RandomAccess
Represents a single row in a CSV (Comma-Separated Values) file. Each row consists of a sequence of elements separated by a delimiter. This class provides methods to manipulate and access elements in the row.

The size of the row is dynamic and can grow as elements are added.

This class implements the Iterable<String> and RandomAccess interfaces, allowing iteration over elements in the row and random access to individual elements by index.

Null elements are not permitted in instances of this class, ensuring consistency in data processing.
